{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0037-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Nested Instances",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1775756671293,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A nested Hobson instance is a complete, independent Hobson environment running inside another. Each nested instance gets its own kernel, its own items, and its own viewport — fully isolated from the parent via ID-prefixed storage and iframe sandboxing."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "You can create one using the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "1c00dfe9-cc76-415d-bb27-451a3cfaacd2"
          },
          {
            "s": "Create Nested Instance"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " item."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "How It Works"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Nesting relies on two mechanisms: "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "storage prefixing in kernel:storage"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "iframe rendering"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " in the view."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Storage Prefixing"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0002-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "bootloader"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " accepts an "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "?instance=<id>"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0031-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "URL parameter"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". When present, the bootloader passes the instance ID to the kernel, and kernel:storage transparently prefixes all operations:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Operation"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Without "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "?instance"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "With "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "?instance=abc"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "save(item)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "stores as "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "item.id"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "stores as "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "abc:item.id"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "get(id)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "looks up "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "id"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "looks up "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "abc:id"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "getAll()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "returns unprefixed items"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "returns "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "abc:*"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " items (stripped)"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The rest of the kernel sees a normal item namespace. "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "33333333-2222-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "kernel:storage"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " handles prefixing and stripping internally via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_prefixId()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_stripPrefix()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " helpers."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Instance ID Chaining"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Nesting composes. When a nested instance creates its own nested instance, the IDs chain:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "parent                → items stored as \"item-id\"\n?instance=abc         → items stored as \"abc:item-id\"\n?instance=abc:def     → items stored as \"abc:def:item-id\""
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "99999999-1111-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "hobson-instance-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " builds the chained ID automatically from "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.getInstanceId()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and the current item's ID."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Iframe Isolation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Each nested instance renders as an iframe pointing to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "bootloader.html?instance=<chainedId>"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". This gives full isolation:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Separate DOM"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — CSS and JavaScript don't leak between instances"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Separate kernel"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — each instance boots its own kernel independently"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Separate items"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — prefixed storage means no item collisions"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No cross-instance communication"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — instances cannot talk to each other (by design)"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Key Items"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Item"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Purpose"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":item-ref",
                {
                  "s": "99999999-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
                },
                {
                  "s": "hobson-instance"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Type definition for instance items"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":item-ref",
                {
                  "s": "99999999-1111-0000-0000-000000000000"
                },
                {
                  "s": "hobson-instance-view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "View that renders the iframe with header and controls"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":item-ref",
                {
                  "s": "f939abc4-2e9e-4d6a-a049-c9361fb3590d"
                },
                {
                  "s": "hobson-instance-lifecycle"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Library that cascade-deletes nested items when an instance is deleted"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Cascade Delete"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Deleting a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "hobson-instance"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " item triggers "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "f939abc4-2e9e-4d6a-a049-c9361fb3590d"
          },
          {
            "s": "hobson-instance-lifecycle"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", which finds all items with the instance's prefix via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.getAllRaw()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and deletes them. This prevents orphaned data in IndexedDB."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "getAll()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " filters out prefixed items (showing only the current namespace), while "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "getAllRaw()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " returns everything — including nested items. The lifecycle library needs "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "getAllRaw()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to find what to clean up."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "API"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Method"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Returns"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.getInstanceId()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Current instance ID, or "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "null"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " if top-level"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.getAllRaw()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "All items including nested-prefixed ones"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Use Cases"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Sandboxed development"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — modify kernel code without risking the parent instance"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "[Testing](item://c0c0c0c0-0036-0000-0000-000000000000)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — isolated storage + isolated DOM + free cleanup = test isolation for free"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Multiple workspaces"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — independent item collections side by side"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Safe experimentation"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — try destructive changes, then just delete the instance"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why No Cross-Instance Communication?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Isolation is the whole point. If instances could talk to each other, they'd need to agree on protocols, handle versioning, and manage shared state — all of which undermines the simplicity of \"just prefix the IDs.\" If you need to move items between instances, export/import is the explicit mechanism."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Prefix Rather Than Separate Databases?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "IndexedDB allows multiple databases, but a single database with prefixed keys is simpler to manage, back up, and inspect. It also makes cascade delete trivial — just filter by prefix."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0002-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Bootstrap"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Where the "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "?instance"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " parameter is parsed and passed to the kernel"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0031-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "URL Parameters"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Documents the "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "?instance"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " parameter alongside "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "?safe"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " and others"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0036-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Testing"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Uses nested instances for test isolation"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "33333333-2222-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
